other_tests.findings: Incisional biopsy showed an embryonal rhabdomyosarcoma.
Examination of a specimen revealed hypolobulated megakaryocytes and rare dysplastic erythroid and myeloid cells.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The proportion of blasts was slightly high, suggesting early neoplastic involvement of the marrow.

other_tests.findings: The smear contained a monomorphous population of medium-sized lymphoid cells, diagnostic of precursor T-lymphoblastic lymphoma.
